[[Image:Bierathlon harrislee.jpg|thumb|right|Kastenlauf participants in [[Harrislee]]]]
'''Kastenlauf''' (literally ''beer crate-running'') or '''Bier-Rallye''', is a drinking game that is played in [[Austria]], [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]]. It is a race among teams that consist of at least two people carrying a crate of [[beer]], the contents of which must be consumed prior to crossing the finish line.<ref>{{in lang|de}} Fuldaer Zeitung [http://www.fuldaerzeitung.de/sixcms/detail.php?template=fz_meldung_04&id=149848 ''Tragischer Unfall beim Fuldaer Kastenlauf''], 19. Juli 2006</ref><ref>{{in lang|de}} [http://www.fsi-philo.uni-wuerzburg.de/it/ueber_uns/index.pdf A 2007 brochure about the Philosophy Department]{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, [[University of Würzburg]]</ref> The first team to cross the finish line after drinking all of their beer is considered the winner. The teams are usually also required to retain all their [[bottle cap]]s, as an anti-[[litter]]ing measure.

The route generally varies from {{convert|5|to|12|km|mi}} in length.<ref>{{cite web|title=Was ist eigentlich ein Kastenlauf?|url=http://www.myheimat.de/aichach/was-ist-eigentlich-ein-kastenlauf-d2388.html|date=June 26, 2006|accessdate=Jan 5, 2011|language=de}}</ref>

In [[Munich]], kastenlauf events have been organized since 1982.<ref>{{in lang|de}} [http://www.mayers-online.de/archiv_4_03.html "Die zehn Kultveranstaltungen im Münchner Uni-Kalender"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20040216224849/http://www.mayers-online.de/archiv_4_03.html |date=2004-02-16 }}, ''[[Mayers]]'' magazine, 2003, no.4</ref> Kastenlaufs are also common among young people while en route to a [[beer festival]], especially on its first day.

